EPODE VIII.

Previous to the general engagement at Actium, there had been several partial engagements between the forces of Augustus and Antony, in which fortune favored the former. Horace, therefore, on hearing of that great battle, which he expected would prove decisive, addressed this epode to his patron Maecenas, then at the scene of action, in anticipation of the glorious result he predicted to his friend.
